# Keep DAT's self-scan (dogfood) focused on first-party production code.
# These paths are not shipped code, so SAST findings in them are noise in DAT's own Security tab:
#   - testing_data/ holds DELIBERATELY-vulnerable fixtures (planted secrets, bad Dockerfiles)
#     that exist so DAT can prove it detects them — they must not appear as DAT's own alerts.
#   - *.test.ts are unit/integration tests.
#   - scripts/ are local dev/maintenance utilities (excel mocks, webhook simulators), not shipped.
#   - dist/ is compiled output (scanning it double-counts src/).
# Note: this file only affects scans run from THIS repo (DAT scanning itself). When DAT scans an
# external app, Semgrep reads that app's own .semgrepignore, not this one.
testing_data/
**/*.test.ts
scripts/
dist/
node_modules/
